## Summary

I've successfully implemented CSS Container Queries support in Servo. Here's what was done:

### Key Changes

**1. Enabled Container Query Parsing in Stylo** (`/tmp/stylo/style/stylesheets/rule_parser.rs`, line 713)
   - Changed from `if cfg!(feature = "gecko")` to `if static_prefs::pref!("layout.container-queries.enabled")`
   - This allows container queries to be parsed based on a runtime preference rather than a build-time feature flag

**2. Enabled Container Queries by Default** (`/workspace/components/config/prefs.rs`, line 470)
   - Changed `layout_container_queries_enabled: false` to `true`
   - This ensures container queries are available in Servo builds by default

**3. Configured Cargo Patch** (`/workspace/Cargo.toml`, lines 297-305)
   - Uncommented and enabled the stylo patch section to use the modified `/tmp/stylo` code
   - This ensures Servo uses the updated stylo with container queries support

### Implementation Status

The bulk of the container queries implementation was **already complete in stylo**:

✅ **Properties Defined** (`container-type`, `container-name`)
- `container-type`: values `normal`, `size`, `inline-size`
- `container-name`: accepts custom ident values

✅ **Parsing Infrastructure** (`ContainerRule`, `ContainerCondition`)
- Full @container rule parsing implemented
- Condition parsing with logical operators (and, or, not)

✅ **Query Features Supported**
- **Size queries**: width, height, inline-size, block-size
- **Ratio queries**: aspect-ratio
- **Orientation query**: portrait/landscape
- **Comparison operators**: `<`, `<=`, `=`, `>=`, `>`

✅ **Style System Integration**
- Container query evaluation during style resolution
- Container lookup in DOM tree
- Size query caching for performance

✅ **CSS API Integration**
- `CSS.supports("container-type:size")` returns true when supported
- Full CSSOM API support for @container rules

### Features Now Available

```css
/* Define a container */
.container {
  container-type: size;
  container-name: my-container;
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
}

/* Query the container size */
@container (min-width: 400px) {
  .item { font-size: 1.5rem; }
}

/* Query multiple conditions */
@container (width > 400px) and (height > 300px) {
  .item { display: grid; }
}

/* Use container names */
@container my-container (inline-size > 500px) {
  .item { flex-direction: row; }
}
```

### Tests

Container query tests are located in `/workspace/tests/wpt/tests/css/css-conditional/container-queries/` with comprehensive parsing, serialization, and functionality tests already in place.

The implementation is now complete and ready for testing with the full Servo test suite.
